message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.CR. This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, specifically in the task of textual entailment. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses biases in the datasets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to reduce biases, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
